<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-11-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-11-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="179" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d179">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">718.1915/622</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Costa Rican Minister</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Beeche</hi></persName>)<note n="23" xml:id="d179fn23">The same, <hi rend="italic">mutatis
                                        mutandis</hi>, to the Panaman Chargé.</note></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-11-18"><hi rend="italic">November 18,
                                        1921</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Minister</hi>: I desire to inform
                                you that Professor O. M. Leland, Dean of the College of Engineering
                                and Architecture of <pb facs="0352" n="228" xml:id="pg_228"/> the
                                University of Minnesota, and Professor John F. Hayford, Director of
                                the College of Engineering of Northwestern University, have been
                                appointed by the Chief Justice of the United States as Commissioners
                                to delimit the boundary between Costa Rica and Panama, in accordance
                                with Article 7 of the Porras–Anderson Treaty of 1910.</p>
                            <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Charles E.
                                Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>